    "body": "Problem:\r\n  set_virttext() recalculates M.box.width from lenght of the last\r\n  message line, causing the box to shrink to that line's width.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\n  Guard the width update so it only runs when the message buffer has exactly one line.\r\n\r\nfixes #33856",
    "closed_at": "2025-05-07T06:48:15Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33877#discussion_r2076249321"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/33877"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/2076249321"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Thanks for looking into it, however I don't think this condition makes much sense. I think this will suffice:\r\n```suggestion\r\n      -- Check if adding the virt_text on this line will exceed the current 'box' width.\r\n      M.box.width = math.max(M.box.width, math.min(o.columns, scol - offset + width))\r\n```",
            "commit_id": "4bd22de2d5422d1c1af24a5f3746ecb6ba6a4488",
            "created_at": "2025-05-06T20:41:46Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -101,7 +101,10 @@ local function set_virttext(type)\n       local offset = tar ~= 'box' and 0\n         or api.nvim_win_get_position(win)[2] + (api.nvim_win_get_config(win).border and 1 or 0)\n \n-      M.box.width = math.min(o.columns, scol - offset + width)\n+      if vim.api.nvim_buf_line_count(ext.bufs.box) == 1 then\n+        M.box.width = math.min(o.columns, scol - offset + width)\n+      end\n+",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33877#discussion_r2076249321",
